<h2 id="expressions">Expressions</h2>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>I shall offer to pay him tomorrow, he will <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="rant and storm about (something)"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(大吹特吹、慷慨激昂地说某事)</code></b> his love for you, and there will be an end of the matter.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Elizabeth had the satisfaction of seeing her father <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="taking pains to"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(十分努力地去做某事)</code></b> to get acquainted with him.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>I cannot <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="fix on"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(选定/确定/敲定)</code></b> the hour, or the spot, or the look, or the words, which laid the foundation.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>And, at length, by repeated assurances that Mr. Darcy was really the object of her choice, by explaining the gradual change which her estimation of him had undergone, relating her absolute certainty that his affection was <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="not the work of a day"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(不是一朝一夕之功)</code></b>, but had stood the test of many months’ suspense, and enumerating with energy all his good qualities, she did conquer her father’s incredulity, and <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="reconcile him to the match"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(使得他同意了这桩亲事)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="If this be the case"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(如若果真如此)</code></b>, he deserves you. I could not have <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="parted with you to any one less worthy; part - (不情愿地)放弃/舍弃某物"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(将你舍弃给一个比你差的人)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Elizabeth’s mind was now <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="relieved from a very heavy weight"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(心中的一块大石头才算了落了地)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Nor was it under many, many minutes, that she could comprehend what she heard, though not in general <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="backward"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(向后的，此处引申为不情愿的)</code></b> to credit what was for the advantage of her family, or that came in the shape of a lover to any of them.</p>
  </li>
</ol>

